    "text": "Erdős Problem #190: declared status 'solved'. Formalized: no. Let $H(k)$ be the smallest $N$ such that in any finite colouring of $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ (into any number of colours) there is always either a monochromatic $k$-term arithmetic progression or a rainbow arithmetic progression (i.e. all elements are different colours). Estimate $H(k)$. Is it true that\\[H(k)^{1/k}/k \\to \\infty\\]as $k\\to\\infty$? Prize: no. Tags: additive combinatorics, arithmetic progressions.",
